<p class="section-title first" align="JUSTIFY"><span style="font-size: 24px;"><b>Welcome to the Chan group! </b></span></p>
&nbsp;
<p class="research-areas" align="JUSTIFY"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Our research focuses on developing novel organic materials with interesting optoelectronic, magnetic, and biological properties. The work in our laboratories involves designing and synthesizing <i>π</i>-conjugated organic molecules and polymers with tailorable physical properties. Some areas of application for these functional materials include organic electronics, energy, and health care.</span></p>
&nbsp;
<p class="research-areas" align="JUSTIFY"><span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong>Open positions</strong></span></p>
&nbsp;
<p class="open-positions" align="JUSTIFY"><span style="font-size: 18px;">We have openings for motivated graduate students, postdoctoral researchers, and UROPs. Interested individuals should contact Dr. Chan (julian.chan@alum.mit.edu).</span></p>
